The paper discusses processing large graphs using distributed systems, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The focus on graph analysis tasks and algorithms such as PageRank and community detection suggests a connection to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The mention of storage and I/O overhead points towards Database Systems (cs.DB). The need for semantics and expressiveness in graph processing suggests a connection to Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the emphasis on resource efficiency and low latency suggests a connection to Machine Learning (cs.LG), as these are important considerations in training and deploying large-scale machine learning models.
